body:
According to the planned [timeline](http://bit.ly/k8s19), we should cut alpha.2 on Wed, Nov 1.

@dashpole Can you try a mock build with [anago](https://github.com/kubernetes/release#instructions-quick-start) to start getting your workstation set up? Let me know if you run into any trouble.

@spiffxp @detiber How far from green are we on [release-master-blocking](https://k8s-testgrid.appspot.com/sig-release-master-blocking) tests? Can we at least have owners for all the failures by a week from now?

According to the proposed schedule, feature freeze is Fri, Oct 27.

I want to send a reminder to k8s-dev soon, but I wanted to check if we're asking for anything different this cycle.

@idvoretskyi Do you require anything at feature freeze other than that the issues are populated in the features repo?

@Bradamant3 There's something in the proposed schedule about "release talking points" and "sig themes" being due at feature freeze time. Can you elaborate on what we need the SIGs to provide?

According to the [timeline](https://github.com/kubernetes/features/blob/master/release-1.9/release-1.9.md#timeline), we should create the `release-1.9` branch and start setting up test infra on Thu Nov 16.

@dashpole You can create the branch with `anago`, and then we'll need you to run `branchff` every day to keep it up to date. Let me or @david-mcmahon know if you have any questions.

@BenTheElder Do you have access to any instructions from previous release test-infra leads on what needs to be set up?

cc PST 

from https://docs.google.com/document/d/1fepegB3d-yCL5RoiuiPd6Ot6mPx2L_MBAl6Q2CEuqrI/edit
@tallclair @cjcullen @liggitt @philips

@AishSundar Following up on our conversation on Slack about adding this to the release handbook.

I'm not entirely sure if this is the right place to add it, but it seems the closest and the question asked on #sig-release was in the context of the branch release management, so this seemed apt.

/cc @AishSundar @sttts @dougm @dims @neolit123
